Indifferent pets is the best solution. What you described above simply will not work.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I said <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>may</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  While I think <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> indifferent pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> might well be the best solution, both for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AFK exping</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> bad pathing</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I can imagine a scenario where <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AFK exping</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would still be possible.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ubaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> attacks my enemies as soon as they attack me, whether they hit or not.  I have noticed this while meditating in the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Karanas</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
I can imagine a fixed spawn point, with odd pathing.  The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AFK Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> stands near the spawn point, possibly at or just beyond combat distance.  The mob spawns, aggros the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and takes a swipe at him.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ubaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> attacks the mob.  The odd pathing then takes the mob <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>away</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> from the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, out of combat distance, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ubaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> becomes the only thing within melee range.<br>
<br>
I know of no specific place where this could be arranged.  Further, it is likely to be extremely rare, or perhaps non-existant.  To the extent that would remain an exploit, it would be of limited use.  Few <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would be able to employ it, and the number of spots where it was possible would be small.   <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> could fix the pathing in those few spots if they remained concerned.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> - It would work as long as the pet refresh cost is &gt; the amount of mana a mage can regenerate while standing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Without checking, it seems to me that I could regen all my mana standing in an hour.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I don't really see how it can be exploited. Solo pulling? Sending in pets to wipe out 1 mob in a group? I'm pretty sure existing game mechanics would already prevent all of this.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Once the pet is engaged, I assume that existing mechanics would come into play, and the pet would be aggroed by mobs near the fight.<br>
<br>
Exploits <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> might</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> exist though, and we need to consider these.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Indifferent Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would radically alter game play for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> All of the other proposals would have side effects for normal, every day playing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I generally agree, but I think we need to consider alternatives.  We must appeal to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with more than emotion and enthusiasm.<br>
<br>
