<br>
The only afk spot I know about that you can get enough xp to even make it worth while (1blue or more in 8 hours 55+) could probably be easily solo'ed by any 49+ magician pet without a DS (a necro pet might even be able to do it, all 50+ melees can easily solo the stuff, they just cant go afk).  VI could easily fix the spot by fixing the mob level, or bumping the mob str up to what it should be for the level the mobs are (mobs are blue to level 60 (level 45+mob), have less then 1200hp, and hit for 60something..Go VI!).  As you can see from the mob stats, this spot is the result of bad programing, and could easily be fixed - not the epic pet being to strong.  All the &quot;epic only&quot; afk spots listed on this site give crap XP (8 hours of afk gives like as much xp as you could in an average xp group in 30minute ish), or are way to risky.<br>
<br>
Best way to fix AFK spots: Fix the mobs that people go afk on.  None of them are mobs that anyone would normally kill (if other people went where the person was afk to hunt, they could train em, or petition to get them kicked because they are asleep or something ,which wouldnt make a good afk spot now would it), so buffing them wouldnt hurt anything else but AFK camps.   <p><font size=1 face="verdana">
